Take two queues 
queue<TreeNode*> q1;
queue<TreeNode*> q2;
Then repeatedly check:
Pop one node from each queue.

Check if both are null.
Are both empty?
    Yes -> continue


Check if exactly one is null.
Is one empty and the other not?
    Yes -> false

    
Check if values differ.
Do they contain different values?
    Yes -> false

    
Push corresponding children.

If the loop finishes without finding a mismatch:

return q1.empty() && q2.empty();

